    <p>All top password managers use AES-256 encryption, but their security architectures differ in subtle, important ways:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Zero-Knowledge Architecture:</strong> This is the industry standard. Your vault is encrypted locally on your device before it is synced to the cloud. The provider never holds your master password or unencrypted data. (1Password, Bitwarden, Dashlane, NordPass, etc.)</li>
